The paper deals with errors in using spreadsheets and analysis of automatic recording of user interaction with spreadsheets. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the analysis of screen captures, which could fall under the Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) category. The paper also mentions the use of spreadsheets in secondary school education, which could fall under the Computer Science and Game Theory (cs.GT) category. The paper also discusses the importance of going from error detection to interaction behaviour analysis, which could fall under the Cybersecurity (cs.CR) category. Finally, the paper discusses the analysis of user preferences and typical approaches in searching for solutions, which could fall under the Computation and Language (cs.CL) category.
